                {
                    "text": "The premise behind what my puzzle is that I will talk to the player, just as I'm doing now.",
                    "time": 10,
                    "tone": "neutral"
                },
                {
                    "text": "And every once in a while I'll say a few things that the user has to pick up on.",
                    "time": 5,
                    "tone": "neutral"
                },
                {
                    "text": "This information will be hidden amongst other dialogue that also help immerse the player into a world full of rich lore and details.",
                    "time": 10,
                    "tone": "neutral"
                }
            ],
            "said": false
        },
        {
            "lines": [
                {
                    "text": "It will be the player's job to figure out what to do with this information. They'll have to complete a task that they normally wouldn't be able to without a piece of information I give them.",
                    "time": 15,
                    "tone": "neutral"
                },
                {
                    "text": "What that task is is still undetermined. Not because I'm lazy but because I prioritized getting the idea of the puzzle actuallized before the actual puzzle itself.",
